**link_data**

This type of ad allows you to add an image alongside a title, a description and
a button.

<%= image_tag "ads/facebook_link_data.png",
  class: 'facebook-ads creative link-data' %>

**type:** `link_data`.
<br>
**spec:** these are the keys you have to provide (see code example):

- `link_data.link` (string): the URL the user will be redirected to when
clithe ad.
- `link_data.message` (string): the main body of the post, above the image.
- `link_data.picture` (string): URL of the ad image.
- `link_data.description` (string): text that appears below the ad image.
- `link_data.call_to_action.type` (string): one of the values defined
in [this page](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/reference/ad-creative-link-data-call-to-action/). Use `OPEN_LINK` for generic ads that take users
to other pages.
- `link_data.call_to_action.value.link_caption` (string): This is the
URL that will show up to the user.
This has to be similar to `link_data.link`.
